Certainly! Below is a concise summary of an article on climate change using LaTeX, focusing on the impact of greenhouse gases on the planet's surface and the resulting changes in weather patterns and ecosystems.

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{amsmath}

\begin{document}

\title{Summary of Climate Change Article}
\author{}
\date{}

\maketitle

\section*{Introduction}
Climate change is a critical global issue primarily driven by the increase of greenhouse gases (GHGs) in the Earth's atmosphere. These gases, including carbon dioxide (\( \text{CO}_2 \)), methane (\( \text{CH}_4 \)), and nitrous oxide (\( \text{N}_2\text{O} \)), trap heat and lead to a warming effect known as the greenhouse effect.

\section*{Impact on Planet's Surface}
The accumulation of GHGs has significant impacts on the Earth's surface:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Global Warming:} The average global temperature has risen, leading to the melting of polar ice caps and glaciers.
    \item \textbf{Sea Level Rise:} As ice melts, sea levels rise, threatening coastal communities and ecosystems.
\end{itemize}

\section*{Changes in Weather Patterns}
The alteration of weather patterns due to climate change is evident:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Extreme Weather Events:} Increased frequency and intensity of hurricanes, floods, droughts, and heatwaves.
    \item \textbf{Altered Precipitation:} Shifts in rainfall patterns, affecting water availability for agriculture and consumption.
\end{itemize}

\section*{Impact on Ecosystems}
Ecosystems are experiencing drastic changes:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Species Migration:} Many species are migrating to cooler areas, disrupting local ecosystems.
    \item \textbf{Biodiversity Loss:} Habitat destruction and changing conditions are leading to a decline in biodiversity.
\end{itemize}

\section*{Conclusion}
The increase in greenhouse gases is a major driver of climate change, affecting the Earth's surface, weather patterns, and ecosystems. Mitigation efforts and adaptation strategies are essential to address these challenges.

\end{document}
```

This LaTeX document provides a structured summary of the key points related to climate change and its impacts. You can compile this code using a LaTeX editor to generate the final document.
